{"id": "duc04-testb-33:6#19", "contents": "Palestinians are growing increasingly uneasy over the appointment of hawkish former Israeli general Ariel Sharon as Netanyahu's foreign minister. Sharon's appointment was seen as a bid to keep far-right allies from toppling Netanyahu's government, and he has been quoted as saying he would refuse to shake the hand of Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat. Erekat described the situation as \"worrisome,\" marking a shift from the Palestinian leadership's previous stance that the appointment was an internal Israeli affair."}
